\section{\texttt{todec}: convert from degrees, minutes and seconds to
  decimal degrees}

\subsection{Use}

\begin{lstlisting}[style=lstchapelf,numbers=none]
proc todec(
   in xmsc: real
): real {
\end{lstlisting}

Here \texttt{xmsc} is a real variable in the form \texttt{gggg.mmss}
where the \texttt{gggg} are the degrees, \texttt{mm} are the minutes and \texttt{ss} the
seconds. For example, \texttt{121.3740} means
\latminsec{121}{37}{40}{}. \texttt{todec} returns a real value in
\emph{decimal} degrees in the form \texttt{gggg.xxxx}. In the case
above, \texttt{todec(121.3740)} returns 121.6278.


